  <body>
   <p>Comrade Benjamin Schlessinger, the president of the International Ladies Garment workers is now visiting Chicago.</p>
   <p>His presence here will be of great benefit to the Skirts and Dress makers. The Joint Board of the Cloak maker locals decided to carry on a campaign to organize the dress and skirt makers. A meeting was held at 180 Washington St., last Monday where the plans of conducting a campaign was reported by organizer Greenberg to an audience of 200 chairladies and a price committee.</p>
